{{Infobox University |name = Texas State University Department of Philosophy |image_name = |image_size = |chairperson = [[Craig Hanks]] |city = [[San Marcos, Texas|San Marcos]] |state = [[Texas]] |website = [http://www.txstate.edu/philosophy/ txstate.edu/philosophy/] |logo = }}
The '''Texas State University Department of [[Philosophy]]''' is an academic division in the College of Liberal Arts at [[Texas State University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Best Philosophy Schools|url=https://www.collegefactual.com/majors/philosophy-and-religious-studies/philosophy/rankings/top-ranked/southwest/texas/|website=[[College Factual]]|accessdate=12 May 2018|language=en|date=20 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Rising Stars: Kandace Lytle|url=https://txstateu.wordpress.com/2011/01/20/rising-stars-kandace-lytle/|website=Bobcat Blog|date=20 January 2011}}</ref> It has particular strengths in [[applied philosophy]], [[moral philosophy]], [[environmental ethics]], [[philosophy of technology]] and [[political philosophy]].
==Philosophy Dialogue Series== The Philosophy Dialogue Series is a forum for the "exchange and critical evaluation of diverse ideas".<ref>{{cite web|title=Philosophy Dialogue Series|url=http://www.txstate.edu/commonexperience/pastsitearchives/2016-2017/events/philosophy-dialogue-series.html|website=www.txstate.edu|accessdate=12 May 2018|language=en|date=8 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=November 7 2013|url=https://issuu.com/universitystar/docs/november_7_2013|website=Issuu|accessdate=12 May 2018|language=en}}</ref> It includes about 60 presentations in each semester and has been held for over 20 years.
==MAAPE== The Master’s Program in Applied Philosophy and Ethics (MAAPE), opened in August 2010, is the largest philosophy master’s program in Texas.<ref>{{cite web|title=Presidential Award Winners 2017|url=http://www.president.txstate.edu/presidential-award-winners.html|website=www.president.txstate.edu|accessdate=12 May 2018|language=en|date=15 June 2017}}</ref>
==Accomplishments== Since the [[Ethics Bowl]] began, the Texas State team has won the regional competition several times and advanced to the national tournament.<ref>{{cite web|title=Texas State team advances to national Ehics Bowl competition|url=https://smmercury.com/2010/11/19/texas-state-team-advances-to-national-ethics-bowl-competition/|publisher=[[San Marcos Mercury]]|accessdate=12 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Rising Stars: The Ethics Bowl Team|url=http://www.liberalarts.txstate.edu/about/risingstars/ethicsbowlteam.html|website=www.liberalarts.txstate.edu|accessdate=12 May 2018|language=en|date=2 August 2017}}</ref>
