'''World Bosniak Congress''' (''WBC'', {{lang-bs|Svjetski bošnjački kongres}}) is a global [[Bosniaks|Bosniak]] organization.<ref name="World Bosniak Congress">{{cite web|title=World Bosniak Congress|url=http://www.balkaninside.com/bosniak-congress/|publisher=Balkan Inside|accessdate=16 May 2014}}</ref> It was founded on 29 December 2012.{{sfn|ICG|26 February 2013}}

It was founded by [[Ferid Muhić]], president of [[Bosniak Academy of Sciences and Arts]], [[Mustafa Cerić]], ex-reisu-l-ulema in Bosnia and Herzegovina and [[Muhamed Filipović]], prominent Bosniak academician. The Congress has a strong presence from [[Sandžak]], a Muslim Bosniak-majority region on the [[Serbia]]-[[Montenegro]] frontier.{{sfn|ICG|26 February 2013}}

WBC is determined as a part of Bosnian revival after [[Bosnian War]] for independence and ethnic cleansing.

